---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="Tyre Size Guide | Spartan Mobile Tyres"
  description="Learn how to read your tyre size. A simple guide to understanding the numbers and letters on your tyre sidewall."
  path="/tyre-size-guide/"
>
  <section class="hero" style="padding: 3.5rem 0 2.5rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Quick guide</span>
      <h1>How to read your tyre size</h1>
      <p>Every tyre has a code on its sidewall. Here is exactly what each part means so you can order the right tyre with confidence.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Visual tyre code display -->
      <div class="tyre-code-wrap">
        <div class="tyre-code" aria-label="Example tyre size 205 55 R16 91V">
          <span class="tc-part" data-label="Width">205</span>
          <span class="tc-sep">/</span>
          <span class="tc-part" data-label="Profile">55</span>
          <span class="tc-sep"> </span>
          <span class="tc-part" data-label="Construction">R</span>
          <span class="tc-part" data-label="Rim size">16</span>
          <span class="tc-sep"> </span>
          <span class="tc-part" data-label="Load">91</span>
          <span class="tc-part" data-label="Speed">V</span>
        </div>
        <p class="tyre-code-note">Hover or tap each number to see what it means</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Breakdown cards -->
      <div class="breakdown-grid">
        <div class="breakdown-card">
          <div class="bc-number">205</div>
          <h3>Section Width</h3>
          <p>The width of the tyre from sidewall to sidewall in millimetres. A bigger number means a wider tyre.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="breakdown-card">
          <div class="bc-number">55</div>
          <h3>Aspect Ratio</h3>
          <p>The height of the tyre sidewall as a percentage of the width. 55 means the height is 55% of 205mm. Lower numbers give a sportier, lower profile look.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="breakdown-card">
          <div class="bc-number">R</div>
          <h3>Construction</h3>
          <p>R stands for Radial, which is the construction type used on almost all modern tyres. You will nearly always see R here.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="breakdown-card">
          <div class="bc-number">16</div>
          <h3>Rim Diameter</h3>
          <p>The diameter of the wheel rim the tyre fits, measured in inches. This must match your wheel exactly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="breakdown-card">
          <div class="bc-number">91</div>
          <h3>Load Index</h3>
          <p>The maximum weight each tyre can carry. 91 means 615kg per tyre. You should never fit a tyre with a lower load index than your vehicle requires.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="breakdown-card">
          <div class="bc-number">V</div>
          <h3>Speed Rating</h3>
          <p>The maximum sustained speed the tyre is rated for. V means up to 149mph. Never fit a tyre with a lower speed rating than your vehicle requires.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="where-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2>Where to find your tyre size</h2>
        <p>You have three easy options.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="where-grid">
        <div class="where-card">
          <div class="where-num">1</div>
          <h3>Tyre sidewall</h3>
          <p>Look at the side of any of your existing tyres. The size is printed in large text, for example <strong>205/55 R16 91V</strong>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="where-card">
          <div class="where-num">2</div>
          <h3>Door sticker</h3>
          <p>Open the driver's door and look at the door frame or sill. Most cars have a sticker showing the recommended tyre size and pressures.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="where-card">
          <div class="where-num">3</div>
          <h3>Vehicle handbook</h3>
          <p>Your car's owner manual will list the approved tyre sizes in the technical specifications section.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Speed rating table -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2>Speed rating reference</h2>
        <p>Common speed ratings and their maximum speeds.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table class="speed-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Letter</th><th>Max speed</th><th>Common use</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>T</td><td>118 mph</td><td>Family cars, SUVs</td></tr>
            <tr><td>H</td><td>130 mph</td><td>Sport saloons, coupes</td></tr>
            <tr><td>V</td><td>149 mph</td><td>Performance cars</td></tr>
            <tr><td>W</td><td>168 mph</td><td>High performance</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Y</td><td>186 mph</td><td>Sports and supercars</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="container cta-inner">
      <div>
        <h2>Know your size? Ready to book?</h2>
        <p>Send us your tyre size and we will give you an instant quote and come to you.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a class="btn" href={`${base}contact/`}>Get a quote</a>
        <a class="btn secondary" href="https://wa.me/447511928899?text=Hi%2C%20I%27d%20like%20a%20quote%20for%20tyres" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">WhatsApp us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* Tyre code display */
  .tyre-code-wrap {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .tyre-code {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.1rem;
    font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 8vw, 5rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem 2.5rem;
  }
  .tc-part {
    position: relative;
    color: var(--accent);
    cursor: default;
    padding: 0 0.05em;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }
  .tc-part::after {
    content: attr(data-label);
    position: absolute;
    bottom: calc(100% + 8px);
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%) scale(0.85);
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    white-space: nowrap;
    opacity: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    transition: opacity 0.15s, transform 0.15s;
  }
  .tc-part:hover::after,
  .tc-part:focus::after {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateX(-50%) scale(1);
  }
  .tc-sep { color: var(--muted); }
  .tyre-code-note {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  /* Breakdown grid */
  .breakdown-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
  }
  .breakdown-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 3px solid var(--accent);
  }
  .bc-number {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--accent);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .breakdown-card h3 { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .breakdown-card p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.93rem; }

  /* Where to find */
  .where-section { background: var(--bg-alt); }
  .where-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
  }
  .where-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .where-num {
    width: 2rem;
    height: 2rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .where-card h3 { margin: 0; }
  .where-card p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.93rem; }
  .where-card strong { color: var(--text); }

  /* Speed table */
  .table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    max-width: 560px;
  }
  .speed-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .speed-table th, .speed-table td {
    padding: 0.8rem 1.25rem;
    text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .speed-table thead th {
    background: var(--surface);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }
  .speed-table tbody tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .speed-table tbody td:first-child {
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .speed-table tbody tr:hover td { background: var(--surface); }

  /* CTA band */
  .cta-band { background: var(--bg-alt); border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .cta-inner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding-top: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .cta-inner h2 { margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .cta-inner p  { margin: 0; }
  .cta-buttons  { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; flex-shrink: 0; }
</style>
